<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Conteúdo de fisl12 marcado com a tag "speeches"</title><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12</link><description>Conteúdo de fisl12 marcado com a tag "speeches"</description><item><title>Call for speakers closed, evaluation will start next friday</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0031/9423/palestras.jpg1305140043" height="148" alt="Palestras" style="float: left; margin-top: 3px; margin-bottom: 3px; margin-left: 6px; margin-right: 6px;" width="225"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Participants registered up to May, 12, will be the evaluators of the speech proposals submitted to fisl12. Closed in May, 9, the call for speakers resulted in 670 proposals. Begining  friday, May, 13, participants registered will  receive their tokens for proposal evaluation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Just like last year, this initiative will allow for community participation in the preparation of the programme grid.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Therefore, if you didn't register for fisl12 yet, you have up to tomorrow to reserve your slot as an evaluator. The registered people will receive an email will an evaluation code. This system, called Swiss Tournament, works like this: the evaluator receives pairs of speech proposals and must choose one. This process, repeated many times between evaluators, allows the best proposals to outstand amongst the others.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 May 2011 17:53:17 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/call-for-speakers-closed-evaluation-will-start-next-friday</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/call-for-speakers-closed-evaluation-will-start-next-friday</guid></item><item><title>Under request, call for speakers is open up to next monday, 9.</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;After receiving a lot of requests by free software community members that couldn't be able to submit their proposals, fisl12 organizing committee decided to give all those late folks a hand, by &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt; postponing the deadline&lt;/span&gt; up to May, 9. It is one more chance for those who wish to see his/her speech in the programme grid of the largest free software event in Latin America. To submit your proposal, &lt;a href="/fisl12/fisl12/chamada-de-trabalhos?lang=en"&gt;click here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;As of May 13, registered &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;participants&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt; will begin to receive their tokens to evaluate the candidate's speeches. Just like last year's edition, the evaluation will be carried on by the swiss tournament method, where the evaluator receives a pair of speeches and must choose one. This process, repeated many times between evaluators, allows to figure out which ones outstand.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 05 May 2011 14:16:32 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/under-request-call-for-speakers-is-open-up-to-next-monday-9.</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/under-request-call-for-speakers-is-open-up-to-next-monday-9.</guid></item></channel></rss>